01:12:04.220 --> 01:12:05.180
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Um,

1360
01:12:05.500 --> 01:12:08.439
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: It is, it is, it is neat.

1361
01:12:08.439 --> 01:12:14.500
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: And and you, in theory, you could even assign all your, because you do have to assign them to their roles, right?

1362
01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:14.502
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Mm-hmm.

1363
01:12:14.500 --> 01:12:31.180
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: You could even assign them all to the shops and do all the farming yourself if you wanted to, but, um, I think one of the ways in which automation benefits this game is because the farms are spread across 4 maps that you have to load between.

1364
01:12:17.000 --> 01:12:18.920
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah, that is absolutely true.

1365
01:12:18.920 --> 01:12:19.640
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: I didn't think about that.

1366
01:12:19.640 --> 01:12:20.119
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: You could.

1367
01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:31.502
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1368
01:12:31.180 --> 01:12:41.079
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Uh, the load times are reasonably good, but you do have to load between them and walk to them as opposed to like a harvest moon or a Stardew, where all of your plants are all generally in the same spot.

1369
01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:41.502
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: That's correct.

1370
01:12:41.079 --> 01:12:57.220
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: I think having automation really benefits it, or else like, man, could you imagine if every day in this game, you had to warp to each town, walk to your plots, water, maintain, and then do it 4 times, like for each town, it would be a nightmare.

1371
01:12:52.000 --> 01:12:52.600
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1372
01:12:56.500 --> 01:12:57.502
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: It would.

1373
01:12:57.220 --> 01:13:00.340
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Like the automation, I think, is really a smart choice.

1374
01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:00.899
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1375
01:13:00.899 --> 01:13:17.399
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah, and they and they introduce it like nice and early, right up front to you, um, which which is clever because, you know, in so many of these other cottage core games, is a whole song and dance, you have to wait X number of days to get your horse, you have to unlock certain things, um, hit certain checkpoints.

1376
01:13:05.500 --> 01:13:07.502
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Yeah, they do.

1377
01:13:17.399 --> 01:13:20.699
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: But here they just kind of throw it all at you, um, which is, again, very nice.

1378
01:13:20.699 --> 01:13:31.800
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: And you know, we're talking about all this functionally, but they make an attempt, like, they give you decorations and stuff like that, just, just for, or not purely aesthetics because they'll give you bonuses and boosts.

1379
01:13:31.800 --> 01:13:36.420
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: But, um, you know, it's also a customisable thing on which, you know, a lot of people.

