1418
01:15:08.939 --> 01:15:24.479
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: In this game, you have to get like a item that is like a tilled soil and put it on the tile, which is which is a little weird when you think about it, and it's definitely against how these things normally go, but you are right in pointing that out.

1419
01:15:14.500 --> 01:15:15.502
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1420
01:15:20.500 --> 01:15:21.340
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1421
01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:34.560
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah, but but that's almost a positive here, to be honest, because one of the things we like around here, again, having gone through, you know, the song you dance so many times.

1422
01:15:24.479 --> 01:15:26.159
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: That is funny.

1423
01:15:26.159 --> 01:15:27.180
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: But it works.

1424
01:15:27.180 --> 01:15:27.779
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: It works.

1425
01:15:34.560 --> 01:15:37.739
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: We like to see different ideas, how you're going to be different, the originality.

1426
01:15:37.739 --> 01:15:41.100
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: So it's interesting at the bare minimum.

1427
01:15:41.000 --> 01:15:41.779
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Yeah.

1428
01:15:41.100 --> 01:15:44.399
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Um, and it, again, feels as well executed clean.

1429
01:15:41.899 --> 01:15:58.460
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: And yeah, even if it goes against genre convention, like normally it would be like you have a bunch of items during your inventory, you take the tailor, you till, you put the seeds in the earth, which is another item, and then you use the watering item to water it, right?

1430
01:15:58.460 --> 01:16:00.619
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: It's like multiple different interactions.

1431
01:16:00.619 --> 01:16:08.600
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: In this game, because of the combat focus, they put like largely combat tools in your item slots, right?

1432
01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:08.502
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Mm-hmm.

1433
01:16:08.600 --> 01:16:10.819
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Like the sword and the fan and the drum.

1434
01:16:10.819 --> 01:16:20.119
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: So I think it made sense in this game to just have, basically you have this magic tiller and that magic tiller just gives you access to like placing things.

1435
01:16:20.119 --> 01:16:24.199
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: You can even use the mouse on the Switch too to like zoom out and just manually.

1436
01:16:22.000 --> 01:16:24.159
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah, mouse mode.

1437
01:16:24.199 --> 01:16:25.699
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Yeah.

1438
01:16:25.699 --> 01:16:54.079
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: And so in that regard, it feels okay to put down like tilled dirt in like that sort of impersonal kind of way, because the structure of your inventory is just not quite the same as how it's handled in other farming games, where like here, yeah, everything is put into one spot here, like buildings and seeds and dirt, whereas in other titles, it's like, well, you're not doing the buildings so much.

1439
01:16:31.500 --> 01:16:32.002
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1440
01:16:39.000 --> 01:16:41.002
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah, you're you're right because.

1441
01:16:45.000 --> 01:16:45.502
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Mm-hmm.

1442
01:16:50.500 --> 01:16:51.460
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1443
01:16:54.079 --> 01:16:54.502
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: So it kind of makes

1444
01:16:58.000 --> 01:17:06.039
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah, no, and I, I mean, I appreciate it, honestly, that's, that's another, that's another big uh, hurdle, a lot of game struggle with.

1445
01:16:58.500 --> 01:16:59.002
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Anyway.

1446
01:17:06.039 --> 01:17:09.640
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Um, invent, like even just the inventory structure.

1447
01:17:09.640 --> 01:17:14.680
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Like, does your game have, you know, a quick access tool belt or whatever, right?

1448
01:17:10.500 --> 01:17:11.002
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Yeah.

1449
01:17:14.680 --> 01:17:19.600
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Do your tools, share inventory with your other items, things like that.

1450
01:17:16.000 --> 01:17:17.439
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Yo, right, yeah.

1451
01:17:19.600 --> 01:17:26.619
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: We see different approaches and sometimes not great ones, lots of times, not great answers to those design challenges.

1452
01:17:26.619 --> 01:17:28.840
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: But this one I think does pretty well.

1453
01:17:28.840 --> 01:17:37.060
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Like you said, a lot of the, uh, your inventor, or it's lots that you're actually equipping and switching out, um, are more combat focussed.

1454
01:17:37.060 --> 01:17:41.800
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Um, you have the tools which do have some functionality on the farm, but, but it's, at least it's very specific.

1455
01:17:41.800 --> 01:17:49.479
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Um, But like your seeds and all that, honestly, you can just chuck them in a storage box and everything in the village is linked.

1456
01:17:43.000 --> 01:17:43.502
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Yeah.

1457
01:17:49.479 --> 01:17:50.319
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: You don't have to think about it.

1458
01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:51.502
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: God, yeah.

1459
01:17:50.319 --> 01:17:59.800
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Which I, Al, I know Al's listening to this and just jumping for joy because he hates that having to dig up stuff or find it from a different area.

