<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: But um, so yeah, so, you know, it's it's convenient if nothing else.

1462
01:18:06.000 --> 01:18:07.140
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: I agree.

1463
01:18:07.140 --> 01:18:10.199
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: I think they made a lot of good choices with item management.

1464
01:18:09.500 --> 01:18:10.399
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1465
01:18:10.199 --> 01:18:16.859
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Like when you hit, if I'm not mistaken, when you hit up on the D-Pad or whatever, it opens up, hang on, I have a game right here.

1466
01:18:16.859 --> 01:18:25.619
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: You hit up on the deep pad, it opens up your inventory, and like the default items at the top are like food and healing items, which is great because you're doing 3rd person action.

1467
01:18:25.619 --> 01:18:30.239
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: And then, like, when you're at the, uh, and oh, yeah.

1468
01:18:30.239 --> 01:18:34.079
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: So, and from here, yeah, you can't see your buildings or anything even.

1469
01:18:34.079 --> 01:18:39.600
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: And then when you're building stuff, all the food and healing items are just hidden because you don't need them in that menu.

1470
01:18:39.600 --> 01:18:52.199
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Lots of good little decisions there, nearly infinite storage capacity for putting stuff away, and like a generous onhand storage capacity for your inventory.

1471
01:18:42.500 --> 01:18:43.002
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1472
01:18:52.199 --> 01:18:53.819
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: Uh, you're right.

1473
01:18:53.819 --> 01:19:03.000
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: These are frictions that I don't tend to to think about because I don't I don't play as many of these games that have 7000 different item types.

1474
01:18:56.500 --> 01:18:57.399
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Mm-hmm.

1475
01:19:02.500 --> 01:19:03.460
<v A2744987-B695-4A4C-99E1-51647E98158F>Kevin: Yeah.

1476
01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:12.659
<v 2FF980F9-DA3C-4AC9-9EB3-E53E62EA5FBB>Liam: But yeah, I think that they made a lot of good choices here in that regard because I don't feel like there's much friction negative.

